gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 106, Pistons 91
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves reached 50 wins for the first time since 2003-04 as they defeated the Pistons, 106-91. Naz Reid led the way for the Timberwolves with 21 points, 10 rebounds and four assists, while Jaden McDaniels added 20 points and four rebounds in the victory. Cade Cunningham put up a game-high 32 points for the Pistons in the losing effort. The Timberwolves win their third game in a row as they improve to 50-22 on the season, while the Pistons fall to 12-61.
